 :tx/rationale "AUDIT F-ARCH-001: Guidance module is 17% of kernel LOC — god module risk. PROBLEM: The guidance system is 14,137 LOC across 4 files (guidance.rs 7,119 + context.rs 2,424 + routing.rs 2,879 + methodology.rs 1,715) — 17% of the 83,293 LOC kernel. By comparison, the core store is 5,848 LOC (7%). The guidance system is larger than store + schema + query + resolution combined. This suggests responsibility absorption: task routing could be a separate module, methodology scoring is a fitness variant, context assembly overlaps with seed.rs. JUSTIFICATION: ADR-STORE-015 (Free Functions Over Store Methods) established the principle that namespace operations should be independent modules. The guidance system violates this by accumulating routing, methodology, and context responsibilities into one mega-module. The god module anti-pattern makes changes risky (touching routing.rs might break methodology.rs) and makes C8 refactoring harder. SOLUTION: No immediate standalone action needed. When C8 refactoring happens (F-C8-004), the guidance split naturally produces: kernel-level guidance_framework (~3K LOC — budget-aware projection, context blocks, output modes) and policy-level ddis_guidance (~11K LOC — basin model, COTX routing, methodology scoring, DDIS-specific telemetry). VERIFICATION: Subsumed by F-C8-004 acceptance criteria. DEPENDENCIES: Subsumed by F-C8-004. The fix is the same work. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs, methodology.rs, routing.rs, context.rs. SEVERITY: Medium. WAVE: 2 (via F-C8-004). EFFORT: Included in F-C8-004 estimate."
